The paper deals with optimization of a multiple access channel, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The use of training sequences and channel estimates suggests a focus on networking and communication (cs.NI). The analysis of a block fading channel and optimization of parameters suggests a systems and control perspective (cs.SY). The consideration of multiuser diversity and achievable rate suggests a focus on multimedia systems (cs.MM). Finally, the use of optimization techniques and closed form expressions suggests a focus on machine learning and optimization (cs.LG).
